Two of his victims were 16 and 17 at the time they were reportedly kidnapped. The third victim's age hasn't been disclosed, but officials say she was a minor at the time.

Court documents detail how Zavala allegedly enticed the three women at different times between 2011 and 2013 to the remote home that he shares with his parents.

The 16-year-old victim told police she was locked in his bedroom and held against her will between March 2011 and May 2011, reports NewsOK.com.

She told police she was allegedly forced to have sexual relations with Zavala 'on an almost daily basis.' 

Scared for her life and feeling isolated, she described his home as 'in the middle of nowhere,' according to an affidavit. 

She became pregnant and then was somehow able to escape. 

Another woman was 17 when she was held captive from January to August 2012.

