During that time, she was punched, strangled, hit with a metal bar and cut with a box knife. 

She, too, was sexually assaulted and became pregnant as a result, but was eventually able to escape.

The third teenage victim began dating Zavala in October 2012. She was homeless at the time and had no family support, and he offered her a place to live. 

But shortly after she moved in, Zavala had her car towed, leaving her with no transportation.

In one particularly violent assault, Zavala allegedly bashed the woman in the head with a hammer multiple times in December 2012, causing a permanent skull deformity. 

When she tried to run from him, he struck her again in the head with the hammer and in the abdomen with a metal bar. 

